  "prompt": "Do employees at Select Income REIT have a good work-life balance? Does this differ across positions and departments?",
  "response": "The work-life balance at Select Income REIT, like at many companies, can vary depending on the position and department. Here\u2019s a general overview based on industry trends and employee feedback:\n\n- **Work-Life Balance**: Overall, work-life balance at Select Income REIT is often reported to be moderate. Employees in some roles, particularly those in administrative or support functions, may experience a better work-life balance compared to those in more demanding roles like asset management, acquisitions, or finance.\n\n- **Positions and Departments**:\n  - **Asset Management and Acquisitions**: These roles tend to involve longer hours and higher stress due to the nature of the work, including deal negotiations and property management responsibilities.\n  - **Finance and Accounting**: Employees in these departments may experience periods of long hours, especially during financial reporting cycles or audits.\n  - **Administrative and Support Roles**: Positions in HR, IT, and office management often report better work-life balance, as these roles typically have more predictable hours.\n  - **Legal and Compliance**: These roles can be intense, particularly during periods of regulatory scrutiny or significant transactions.\n\nFactors such as company culture, management expectations, and individual workload also play a significant role in determining work-life balance. It\u2019s always a good idea to speak with current employees or read reviews on platforms like Glassdoor for more specific insights tailored to individual roles.",
